{#- ═══ INDIANA PRICING. t-prose (dc-base chrome). Mirrors the proven DE/NY pricing body
    (find-an-accountant/delaware/pricing.njk): TL;DR (#in-pricing-tldr, speakable) · engagement
    shapes · full pricing vs-table (.cmp, canonical IN figures) · why fixed-fee · includes ·
    firm-level expert review (no founder name, NO address — areaServed-only) · related. hero /
    in-brief / ai-summary / faq / final CTA are layout-owned (t-prose) from the .11tydata arrays
    + sec.aiH/faqH. Canonical IN pricing only (IN-FACTS): from-$400/mo monthly · from-$1,200
    cleanup/catch-up · from-$750 QB setup · from-$1,200 QB cleanup · from-$250/mo sales tax ·
    from-$300 county income tax (withholding) · from-$1,500/mo fractional CFO. ═══ -#}

{#- TL;DR · how IN pricing works. #in-pricing-tldr = speakable. (H2: How TechBrot Indiana pricing works.) -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="in-pricing-tldr">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">In one paragraph</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">How TechBrot Indiana pricing works.</h2>
    <div class="tldr-prose">{%- for p in tldr %}<p{% if loop.first %} id="in-pricing-tldr-body"{% endif %}>{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}</div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- ENGAGEMENT SHAPES · three pricing models → r-3 dc-card. (H2 + 3 H3s) -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="in-pricing-shapes">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Three engagement shapes</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Every Indiana engagement fits one of three shapes.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:68ch;">Pricing structure follows the shape of the work. All three run to the same standard: fixed fee, written scope, named ProAdvisor.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for s in shapes %}
      <div class="dc-card"><span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ s.tag | safe }}</span><h3>{{ s.title | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ s.body | safe }}</p><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:8px 0 0;">{{ s.examples | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- FULL PRICING · every IN service + range → vs-table→.cmp. Canonical IN figures. (H2: Every Indiana service, every range.) -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="in-pricing-ranges" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">All pricing</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Every Indiana service, every range.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 24px;max-width:70ch;">The complete pricing landscape for Indiana businesses. Every fee is fixed and scoped in writing before work begins.</p>
    <table class="cmp">
      <caption class="sr-only">TechBrot fixed-fee starting pricing across every Indiana service.</caption>
      <thead><tr><th scope="col">Service</th><th scope="col">Engagement type</th><th scope="col">Fee range</th><th scope="col">Cadence</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        {%- for r in ranges %}
        <tr>
          <th scope="row" data-col="Service">{% if r.href %}<a href="{{ r.href }}">{{ r.service | safe }}</a>{% else %}{{ r.service | safe }}{% endif %}</th>
          <td data-col="Engagement type" style="color:var(--color-ink-mute);">{{ r.type | safe }}</td>
          <td class="num us" data-col="Fee range"><strong>{{ r.fee | safe }}</strong></td>
          <td data-col="Cadence" style="color:var(--color-ink-mute);">{{ r.cadence | safe }}</td>
        </tr>
        {%- endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p class="prose" style="font-size:13.5px;color:var(--color-ink-mute);margin-top:14px;">{{ rangesNote | safe }}</p>
  </div>
</section>

{#- WHY FIXED-FEE · standing brand line as H2; body carried as prose. (H2: Why we don't bill by the hour.) -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="in-pricing-why">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Why fixed-fee</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:14px;">Why we don&rsquo;t bill by the hour.</h2>
    <div class="prose">{%- for p in whyBody %}<p>{{ p | safe }}</p>{%- endfor %}</div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- INCLUDES · six standards every fixed fee carries → r-3 dc-card. (H2 + 6 H3s) -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="in-pricing-includes" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">What&rsquo;s always included</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Every fixed fee includes these.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:66ch;">Regardless of service or price, every Indiana engagement includes the same six standards. They&rsquo;re not add-ons &mdash; they&rsquo;re the baseline.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for inc in includes %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{{ inc.title | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ inc.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- EXPERT REVIEW · firm-level, no founder name, NO address (areaServed-only). (H2: Indiana pricing maintained by the TechBrot ProAdvisor team.) -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="in-pricing-review">
  <div class="ct read">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Pricing standards</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:18px;">Indiana pricing maintained by the TechBrot ProAdvisor team.</h2>
    <div class="byline">
      <div class="byline__mark" aria-hidden="true" style="background:var(--color-accent);"></div>
      <div>
        <p class="byline__name">By the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team</p>
        <p class="byline__review">TechBrot Inc. &middot; Independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="prose" style="margin-top:20px;">
      <p>Pricing on this page is maintained by the Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor team at <strong>TechBrot Inc.</strong>, an independent ProAdvisor firm serving Indiana businesses remotely across all 92 counties. Ranges reflect current operational starting pricing for Indiana engagements and are reviewed periodically; specific fixed fees are quoted per engagement after a free discovery call. Indiana tax references &mdash; the flat 7% statewide sales tax with no local add-ons, the flat 2.95% state income tax for 2026, and the local income tax levied by all 92 counties on top of the state rate &mdash; reflect <a href="https://www.in.gov/dor/" rel="noopener nofollow">Indiana Department of Revenue</a> rules current as of the date below; per-county local income-tax rates are set by each county and published in the <a href="https://www.in.gov/dor/i-am-a/individual/individual-income-county-tax-rates-by-year/" rel="noopener nofollow">DOR county-rate list</a>. TechBrot performs bookkeeping and QuickBooks work and coordinates with your CPA, who files; it does not file Indiana returns, the county income-tax return, or the sales-tax return.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="trust-row">
      {%- for c in reviewCreds %}
      <div class="trust-row__item"><p class="trust-row__value">{{ c.label }}</p><p class="trust-row__label">{{ c.detail | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- if not loop.last %}<div class="trust-row__divider"></div>{%- endif %}
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="meta-reviewed"><span>Published: 2026-06-26</span><span>Updated: 2026-06-26</span><span>Reviewed: 2026-06-26 &middot; Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor</span></p>
  </div>
</section>

{#- RELATED · where to go next → r-2 dc-card hub-card. (H2: Where to go next. + 4 H3s) -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="in-pricing-related">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Related</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:24px;">Where to go next.</h2>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for r in related %}
      <a class="dc-card hub-card" href="{{ r.href }}"><h3>{{ r.title | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;color:var(--color-ink-mute);">{{ r.body | safe }}</p><span class="hub-card__go">{{ r.cta | safe }} <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></span></a>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
